The paper deals with wireless powered networks, which are typically studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The optimization problem formulation and solution methods involve mathematical programming and control theory, which are relevant to the systems and control (cs.SY) and machine learning (cs.MA) sub-categories. The paper also presents numerical results and performance analysis, which are relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
